The U.S. is set to overtake  Russia  as
the worldâ€™s largest producer of crude and natural gas, according
to analysis by  Wall Street Journal .  The U.S. produced about 22 million barrels of oil
equivalent a day of crude, natural gas and other petroleum
liquids in July, according to the WSJ, using data from the U.S.
Energy Information Administration and the  International Energy
Agency . Russia will produce 21.8 million barrels of oil
equivalent a day in 2013, the WSJ said, citing Russian
government forecasts.  To contact the reporter on this story:
